Package ss.pentago.model.board

Enum Marble

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<Marble>
      • ss.pentago.model.board.Marble
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Marble>
    public enum Marble
extends java.lang.Enum<Marble>
    Marble represents the state a field on the Board can be in, which is either empty, or held by either of two players, identified by black and white.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant Description
      BLACK
      Represents the player who moves first.
      EMPTY
      Represents an empty spot on the board.
      WHITE
      Represents the player who moves second.
